& [SLMSlice46UncertaintyBoundaryStabilizationRules] is a work-ready slice for bounded uncertainty identities
  + [slice_id] is SLM-46
  + [status] is verified_wsl
  + [effort] is M-L
  + [risk] is medium
  + [depends_on] is SLM-08, SLM-09, SLM-32, SLM-45
  + [scope] is define when uncertainty itself has stable enough boundaries to enter SemanticGraph
  + [acceptance_criteria] is unresolved_role, unresolved_scope, and provider_disagreement have separate stabilization criteria
  + [proof_route] is fixture expansion plus WSL cargo test

  ! [CompletionEvidence] is the SLM-46 verification record
    @ [contract] is slm_project/specifications/contracts/SLM_Uncertainty_Boundary_Stabilization_Contract.sop
    @ [source_gate] passed python slm_project/tools/slm_source_gate_check.py
    @ [wsl_cargo_test] passed 15 tests
    @ [self_check] passed slm_self_check
    @ [demo] uncertainty list includes unresolved_subject_boundary, unresolved_role, and unresolved_scope
